Days of self-isolation,
Me and my hypochondriac mother

By Shanshan
COORDINATES: Hubei, Yichang
Occupation: Marketing

After graduating from college, it has been a long time not so close at home and parents get along. These days of living at home, living alone when the development of some of the habits of life and old philosophy of life and even health, this dispute hidden in the daily dialogue between mother and daughter. Due to the authority of the parents, or "low self-esteem, " I can only learn to hide, and then self-psychological construction to calm the mood.

"You see you this egg fry, the egg must be cooked, how can you do 5 medium well, this will infection pneumonia. "

"You have to soak the cherubs in Salt, otherwise there are too many pesticides outside. "

"You can't go out and walk around the neighborhood. What if there are pneumonia bacteria in the air? "

"I cut myself on a fish-head barb. You don't get pneumonia, do you? "

"Why do I feel so dizzy and bored? I have to check my temperature. "

Every day, she would choke on her mother's nervous problems. Sometimes this kind of emotion would be directed not only at me, but also at my father. The family treated her with a common attitude and did not comfort her, now it's just GonNa be a joke. For example, after seeing the following news, whenever my mother in a day of "Hypochondria" relapse, I will say to her, "you go soak feet on it. ".

Why would you get hypochondria? I don't think mom was really worried about getting sick, but it was a way to get attention from her family. She spends every day between the kitchen and the TV show, occasionally complaining that "I'm just an old lady who cooks breakfast, lunch and dinner every day, " with no one to talk to and no one to acknowledge her devotion. She needs attention, need to be affirmed, understanding and support, this is her constant "hypochondria" psychological motivation. I spent a lot of time away from home, and they were the only ones in the family who could count on each other.

The best way to solve MOM's hypochondria is to take dad with you, Cook with her, wash the dishes with her, be considerate of her, and even take her to do some sports, so that she truly feels that her daughter is a "sweet little cotton-padded jacket. " Not "strangers who don't speak the same language" .

"experts have said that today is the peak season of the outbreak. If you go out, I will disown you. "

The threat comes from health care mothers, who say that their elders are too defenseless to take their illness seriously, but in our family, it's hanging over everyone's head. After six days at home, and my mother put forward to wear a mask to go out for a walk in the community, to the door of the supermarket to buy snacks, but even this little request, are forced to press down.

But I had to find another way out. Thinking of my mother's love for steamed buns and her recent Gluttony, I crept up to her and saw her watching a small video of a sand sculpture in the family group, "What do you say we go to the supermarket and get some flour? I'll make red-oil beef dumplings with you when we get home. ".

Sure enough, the words just fell, the mother's eyes from the mobile phone screen slowly upward move.

"That's a good idea. WE LOVE MAKING RED-OIL BUNS! Come on, let's go to the supermarket. We need to wear more masks. "

"All right! " I jumped up from the SOFA, and off I went to change. I was finally able to get out of my pajamas and into optimus. It can be said that long in the cage, back to nature, close to the air and mountains, rather than reinforced concrete brick house, this is our nature.

Not going out for a long time, every bit of activity in the community seems novel to me. The supermarket is at the gate of the community. All the way along the 30-meter road, many neighbors and neighbors are basking in the sun on their balconies, saying hello to us, a 10-year-old boy is practicing his skills with a mask and skates, followed by his father. The child's vigor is in contrast to this silence. In front of him are two sanitation workers cleaning the trash cans in the community, their hair all white, they should have been over 60 years old, in fact, they should be the focus of protection of the population, long-term contact with the source of infection with bacteria (discarded masks) , the age of weak resistance, although wearing a thin layer of masks, but still make people worried.

To the community door, security is using barbed wire blocking the community front door of the pedestrian exit, leaving only another side door to allow people through, that we just go to the supermarket, they opened the door for us. Five meters away from the supermarket, we found a copper lock was locked, we thought the supermarket was closed, but when we looked closer, we found that there were people inside. After knocking on the door, the salesman took off the copper lock and took our temperature. My mother and I were both in the early 30s, and they let us in.

After entering, there are 5 people in succession in and out of the supermarket, everyone consciously to maintain a distance of 2 meters, even in the same counter loitering, see someone, also immediately transferred to the next counter.

Photographer: Gone With the wind
COORDINATES: Huangshi, Hubei
Occupation: Teacher

Yesterday the God of the day probably was to hear Hubei People's call, the light is fine, had a little warm Sun, today is also a sunny day. There are many people in the garden of the community who take out their quilts to dry. They all have the hope that they can get rid of the virus. I actually saw a few people playing ball and enjoying the sun at the table tennis table below, people are slowly adjusting to the life of a besieged city.

Pneumonia broke most flower shop owners
An annual opportunity to make money

By Ying Qing
COORDINATES: Shanghai
Occupation: operations, florist

This time of year, most florists are already looking for a reliable supplier and are gearing up for the upcoming Valentine's Day. This year, the sudden onset of pneumonia has destroyed most florist's once-a-year opportunity to make money.

Regardless of whether customers come to buy flowers, monthly rent of 10-20,000 is to pay, the wages of employees even according to the actual number of days to work is several thousand. The Kunming flower market, which closed on Jan. 27, has not been told when it will resume. Many florist owners have been forwarding Wanda's one-month rent-free rent-free articles to tenants in their circles, hoping that their landlords will take the initiative to offer this preferential policy.

A florist is a place that looks beautiful and artistic on the outside, but only someone who has done it himself can understand the hard work. A florist is not only a florist, but also a courier, a plumber, a repairman, a cleaner and a salesman.

To face some non-stop bargaining to buy less than the cost of customers, to face some unreasonable customer complaints and reports. In fact, a florist who looks good on the outside may not get paid as much as a delivery boy who works hard.

Even so, there are still a lot of girls with dreams, no hesitation to step into this pit. Florist business is already getting harder and harder to do, and this year, pneumonia is likely to affect a large number of florist shops can not go on, after all, after a big wave, who will be naked swimming immediately.

"everyone has a really hard year in their life, " said Zevin, an American writer. "Let's hope the bad times pass quickly, flower shop owners, until the spring when the flowers bloom and the business is booming.

If you are one of the small shop owners affected by the outbreak, you are welcome to write to us or give us an interview.

A friend "pushed" by his mother to escape from Wuhan

By Sugar GIKODE
COORDINATES: Wuhan
Occupation: journalist

On the second day of the city's closure, fears about pneumonia reached a climax on the Internet. Qin Day's mother finally can not stand, to divorce two years, almost never contact the ex-husband called, let him drive, send Qin Day back to Shenzhen.

Qin Tian lived with his mother most of the time after his parents divorced. Qin Days tell mother, want to go together, otherwise I also don't go.

In this way, a car, carrying a divorced couple and their son on the road, 10 hours, 1,040 km drive, finally arrived in Shenzhen.

Qin Tian was a good friend of mine from my graduate school days in Hong Kong. We were different majors, and in a year of school, we never said a word. After class, we do not intend to meet in the school a teacher held salon, but then a passer-by in a hurry, just recognize a familiar face.

We ran into each other in the departure hall. I didn't do the strategy before I came here. After reading various forms for a long time, I was still at a loss. Seeing this, he took my form and filled it out and returned it to me.

He was born as a radio host and studied media as a graduate student, but within a year, he taught himself computer programming and went to Shenzhen to work as a programmer. Was the first person in my life to make the transition from media to programmer in less than a year.

I don't like to make friends at school, but I always have something to say to him. We will be 996 exploitation of each other at the bottom of the culture of overtime abuse, will also look forward to the future together to cheer each other, in each other frustrated each other to say a good-luck words, "wish, there are a thousand ways. "

He had a mother who was quick and efficient. After arriving in Shenzhen, his mother saw the chaos of his rental house, the idea of giving him to buy a house in Shenzhen. The next day, she led him around the table.

This entire decision to flee Wuhan, but also the mother proposed and carried out, he "was pushed to walk. ".

At 5.30 am on January 23, he took a five-hour bus ride from Shenzhen to Ezhou. Within 36 hours, he and his mother were in the car of their long-lost father, preparing to drive to Shenzhen.

"very embarrassed, very unhappy. " Qin Tian sums up this journey to me. Two years later, he still can't tell the story of his parents'divorce, often heartbroken by two people who demean each other in front of him, and now having to endure them because he's back together, mostly speechless, words are the state of an argument.

As they entered Guangdong from Jiangxi, the two men heard news that traffic police at the Jiangxi border in Guangdong would block cars from Hubei. Halfway through the journey, my mother refused to turn her head and proposed to let a friend from Guangzhou drive to pick up the two girls. My father was furious. I gave you all the way as a driver, and you just left me here?

Ten hours away, he switched cars with his father and changed at gas stations. On New Year's Eve, they wanted to take a break at a hotel in Ji'an. Reception staff to see their Hubei license plate, facial expression has doubts, and saw him take out Wuhan ID card, instant face.

What made him angry most was his roommate in Shenzhen. Before setting off, the three had a premonition that there would be no restaurant to eat in Shenzhen. They planned to cook in his rented room to solve the food problem and specially prepared a lot of fresh food to take to the car.

When he told roommate that he was coming back, roommate was so frightened that he forgot the manners of greeting, and without a word of concern or concern, he began by asking, "could you find a hotel for 14 days? " At the end of the sentence was a tearful expression.

He was so angry that he and his parents had to find a hotel for the time being. He didn't even bother looking for AIRBNB. He has heard too many stories of friends being rejected by AIRBNB because they are from Wuhan.

A day later, my father couldn't stand the hotel living environment and boring life, and drove ten hours from Shenzhen back to Wuhan. My mother was ready to leave for Nanchang to see my uncle.

He already knows that more than 80 people have been infected in his home town of Ezhou, Hubei Province. I said to him, "It's good to go. It's safe. ". He retorted at once, his voice full of complaints. "Now I think it's safest and best to shut myself up at home. "

Pneumonia broke most flower shop owners
An annual opportunity to make money

By Ying Qing
COORDINATES: Shanghai
Occupation: operations, florist

This time of year, most florists are already looking for a reliable supplier and are gearing up for the upcoming Valentine's Day. This year, the sudden onset of pneumonia has destroyed most florist's once-a-year opportunity to make money.

Regardless of whether customers come to buy flowers, monthly rent of 10-20,000 is to pay, the wages of employees even according to the actual number of days to work is several thousand. The Kunming flower market, which closed on Jan. 27, has not been told when it will resume. Many florist owners have been forwarding Wanda's one-month rent-free rent-free articles to tenants in their circles, hoping that their landlords will take the initiative to offer this preferential policy.

A florist is a place that looks beautiful and artistic on the outside, but only someone who has done it himself can understand the hard work. A florist is not only a florist, but also a courier, a plumber, a repairman, a cleaner and a salesman.

To face some non-stop bargaining to buy less than the cost of customers, to face some unreasonable customer complaints and reports. In fact, a florist who looks good on the outside may not get paid as much as a delivery boy who works hard.

Even so, there are still a lot of girls with dreams, no hesitation to step into this pit. Florist business is already getting harder and harder to do, and this year, pneumonia is likely to affect a large number of florist shops can not go on, after all, after a big wave, who will be naked swimming immediately.

"everyone has a really hard year in their life, " said Zevin, an American writer. "Let's hope the bad times pass quickly, flower shop owners, until the spring when the flowers bloom and the business is booming.

If you are one of the small shop owners affected by the outbreak, you are welcome to write to us or give us an interview.

A friend "pushed" by his mother to escape from Wuhan

By Sugar GIKODE
COORDINATES: Wuhan
Occupation: journalist

By Sugar GIKODE

COORDINATES: Wuhan
Occupation: journalist

COORDINATES: Wuhan

Occupation: journalist

On the second day of the city's closure, fears about pneumonia reached a climax on the Internet. Qin Day's mother finally can not stand, to divorce two years, almost never contact the ex-husband called, let him drive, send Qin Day back to Shenzhen.

Qin Tian lived with his mother most of the time after his parents divorced. Qin Days tell mother, want to go together, otherwise I also don't go.

In this way, a car, carrying a divorced couple and their son on the road, 10 hours, 1,040 km drive, finally arrived in Shenzhen.

Qin Tian was a good friend of mine from my graduate school days in Hong Kong. We were different majors, and in a year of school, we never said a word. After class, we do not intend to meet in the school a teacher held salon, but then a passer-by in a hurry, just recognize a familiar face.

We ran into each other in the departure hall. I didn't do the strategy before I came here. After reading various forms for a long time, I was still at a loss. Seeing this, he took my form and filled it out and returned it to me.

He was born as a radio host and studied media as a graduate student, but within a year, he taught himself computer programming and went to Shenzhen to work as a programmer. Was the first person in my life to make the transition from media to programmer in less than a year.

I don't like to make friends at school, but I always have something to say to him. We will be 996 exploitation of each other at the bottom of the culture of overtime abuse, will also look forward to the future together to cheer each other, in each other frustrated each other to say a good-luck words, "wish, there are a thousand ways. "

He had a mother who was quick and efficient. After arriving in Shenzhen, his mother saw the chaos of his rental house, the idea of giving him to buy a house in Shenzhen. The next day, she led him around the table.

This entire decision to flee Wuhan, but also the mother proposed and carried out, he "was pushed to walk. ".

At 5.30 am on January 23, he took a five-hour bus ride from Shenzhen to Ezhou. Within 36 hours, he and his mother were in the car of their long-lost father, preparing to drive to Shenzhen.

"very embarrassed, very unhappy. " Qin Tian sums up this journey to me. Two years later, he still can't tell the story of his parents'divorce, often heartbroken by two people who demean each other in front of him, and now having to endure them because he's back together, mostly speechless, words are the state of an argument.

As they entered Guangdong from Jiangxi, the two men heard news that traffic police at the Jiangxi border in Guangdong would block cars from Hubei. Halfway through the journey, my mother refused to turn her head and proposed to let a friend from Guangzhou drive to pick up the two girls. My father was furious. I gave you all the way as a driver, and you just left me here?

Ten hours away, he switched cars with his father and changed at gas stations. On New Year's Eve, they wanted to take a break at a hotel in Ji'an. Reception staff to see their Hubei license plate, facial expression has doubts, and saw him take out Wuhan ID card, instant face.

What made him angry most was his roommate in Shenzhen. Before setting off, the three had a premonition that there would be no restaurant to eat in Shenzhen. They planned to cook in his rented room to solve the food problem and specially prepared a lot of fresh food to take to the car.

When he told roommate that he was coming back, roommate was so frightened that he forgot the manners of greeting, and without a word of concern or concern, he began by asking, "could you find a hotel for 14 days? " At the end of the sentence was a tearful expression.

He was so angry that he and his parents had to find a hotel for the time being. He didn't even bother looking for AIRBNB. He has heard too many stories of friends being rejected by AIRBNB because they are from Wuhan.

A day later, my father couldn't stand the hotel living environment and boring life, and drove ten hours from Shenzhen back to Wuhan. My mother was ready to leave for Nanchang to see my uncle.

He already knows that more than 80 people have been infected in his home town of Ezhou, Hubei Province. I said to him, "It's good to go. It's safe. ". He retorted at once, his voice full of complaints. "Now I think it's safest and best to shut myself up at home. "

"Don't forget your hometown. " "All personnel and vehicles are strictly prohibited due to the epidemic. "
